    {
      "title": "Conditional Particles Causing Jazm",
      "titleArabic": "أدوات الشرط الجازمة",
      "content": [
        "Conditional particles that cause jazm include إِنْ (if), مَنْ (whoever), مَا (whatever), and others. Both the condition and response clauses are affected."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "إِنْ: if (general condition)",
        "مَنْ: whoever (for people)",
        "مَا: whatever (for things)",
        "كَمْ interrogative and predicative forms"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "إِنْ تَدْرُسْ تَنْجَحْ", "english": "If you study, you will succeed" },
        { "arabic": "مَنْ يَعْمَلْ خَيْرًا يَجِدْهُ", "english": "Whoever does good will find it" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Doubled Verbs (الفعل المضعّف)",
      "titleArabic": "الفعل المضعّف",
      "content": [
        "Doubled verbs have the same letter as both second and third radicals. When conjugated with sukūn-beginning suffixes, the doubled letters separate; otherwise they remain together."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Second and third radicals are identical",
        "Letters separate with sukūn suffix: مَرَرْتُ, رَدَدْتُ",
        "Letters stay together otherwise: يَمُرُّ, يَرُدُّ",
        "Common verbs: مَرَّ, رَدَّ, ظَنَّ, شَكَّ, حَلَّ"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "مَرَّ - يَمُرُّ - مَرَرْتُ", "english": "to pass by" },
        { "arabic": "رَدَّ - يَرُدُّ - رَدَدْتُ", "english": "to return/reply" },
        { "arabic": "ظَنَّ - يَظُنُّ - ظَنَنْتُ", "english": "to think/suppose" }
      ]
    }
  ],
